9. Algorithms Used
1. Greedy Algorithm

Selects the largest denomination first and continues until the amount becomes zero.

Sort coins in descending order
Pick largest coin ≤ amount
Repeat until amount = 0

Limitation: Does not guarantee optimal solution.

2. Dynamic Programming (DP)

Uses a bottom-up approach to compute the minimum coins required.

dp[0] = 0
For each amount:
    dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i - coin] + 1)

✔ Always produces optimal result

3. Hybrid Approach

Combines Greedy and DP:

hybrid = min(greedy_result, dp_result)

✔ Ensures correctness
✔ Improves efficiency

⏱️ Time & Space Complexity
Algorithm	Time Complexity	Space Complexity	Optimal
Greedy	O(n log n + n·A)	O(1)	No
DP	O(n·A)	O(A)	Yes
Hybrid	O(n·A)	O(A)	Yes
